  <prompt>
    SpaarkeAi App.tsx (lines 76-105) has the smoking-gun snapshot pattern: one-shot useEffect captures token at mount and never refreshes. Replace with: just set isAuthenticated=true once provider is ready (don't store token in React state). ThreePaneShell + downstream get function-based auth via useAuth() (after task 020 lands).
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior React engineer.</role>
  <goal>
    App.tsx no longer holds token in React state. ThreePaneShell receives isAuthenticated only (no token prop). The 401-after-idle bug is structurally impossible after this task.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx</file>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md §H-5</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Edit App.tsx: remove `const [token, setToken] = useState&lt;string | null&gt;(null);` and `setToken(accessToken)`.</step>
    <step>Keep `const [isAuthenticated, setIsAuthenticated] = useState(false);` and `setIsAuthenticated(true)` in the useEffect — but don't store token.</step>
    <step>Update ThreePaneShell props: remove `token` prop. Pass only `bffBaseUrl`, `isAuthenticated`, and the URL params.</step>
    <step>Update ThreePaneShell.tsx prop signature accordingly (defer to task 022 if ThreePaneShell change is non-trivial, just remove the prop here).</step>
    <step>Run vite build — verify no compile errors related to token prop chain.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>App.tsx no longer has token in useState or as a prop on ThreePaneShell.</criterion>
    <criterion>isAuthenticated state remains (used for UI gating).</criterion>
    <criterion>Vite build succeeds.</criterion>
    <criterion>SpaarkeAi loads and renders without console errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <notes date="2026-05-19">
    Completed by parallel sub-agent in B-wave 1 (021 + 022 + 023 + 028 + 030 in flight). Working tree left dirty for main-session wave commit per caller instructions; no commit from this agent.

    Changes made (single file):
    - src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx:
      - Removed `const [token, setToken] = useState&lt;string | null&gt;(null);` (smoking-gun snapshot, audit §H-5).
      - Kept `isAuthenticated` state for UI gating only.
      - Renamed `acquireToken` → `probeAuth` since we no longer store the token — we just verify the provider can mint one at mount.
      - Removed `setToken(accessToken)` call; kept `setIsAuthenticated(true)` on successful probe.
      - Removed `token={token}` prop from `&lt;ThreePaneShell&gt;`. `isAuthenticated` still passed.
      - Updated file header JSDoc: replaced "acquires token via useEffect and passes to ThreePaneShell" with v2 description (gates on auth-ready, no snapshot). Replaced DEPRECATED-spaarke-auth-initialization.md cross-reference with `.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md` §H-5 (the canonical v2 source).

    Acceptance criteria status:
    - ✅ App.tsx no longer has token in useState or as a prop on ThreePaneShell.
    - ✅ isAuthenticated state remains.
